\begin_layout Standard
i) 
\emph on
The word "ignition" is not used quite in the way it is usually used.
 Ignition often implies a sudden rate change that changes the heat generation
 in the system and an accompanying t increase.
 The authors should either give their definition of what they mean by ignition
 or use a different word (inspect e.g.
 how " catalytic ignition" is used in the relevant literature.
\end_layout

